name: Recombinant Honeycomb
description: A honeycomb with strange properties that can provide great healing.

name: Arctic Honeycomb
description: A frozen honeycomb! Eat it!

name: Arid Honeycomb
description: A sandy honeycomb.

name: Copper Honeycomb
description: This honeycomb has high copper content.

name: Durasteel Honeycomb
description: A honeycomb made of solid durasteel.

name: Rotcomb
description: Laced with unusual chemicals. Extremely psychotropic.

name: Reaper Honeycomb
description: Possesses a meaty taste that resembles pork, and is rich with red honey.

description: An aromatic honeycomb. Low grade healing.

description: A delicious forest honeycomb! Low grade healing.

name: Earthen Honeycomb
description: This earthy comb increases max health by 25%

name: Moon Honeycomb
description: A honeycomb with unusual gravitational abilities if consumed.

name: Harlequin Honeycomb
description: A honeycomb that contains strong anti-shadow properties.

name: Stellar Honeycomb
description: A comb that is said to be infused with mystical healing energy.

name: Shrouded Honeycomb
description: Cosmic antimatter energy infuses this comb. Grants Shadow Taint immunity.

name: Plutonium Honeycomb
description:
RADIOACTIVE! DO NOT EAT!
+2 Fuel

name: Crystalline Honeycomb
description: A glittering honeycomb with small particles of pure crystal within.

name: Radioactive Honeycomb
description:
RADIOACTIVE! DO NOT EAT!
+1 Fuel

name: Red Honeycomb
description: A delicious red honeycomb. Smells like meat.

name: Silk Honeycomb
description: This honeycomb is packed full of silk. Not tasty, but still medicinal.

name: Silver Honeycomb
description: This honeycomb has high silver contents. Great poison resistance.

name: Solarium Honeycomb
description:
RADIOACTIVE! DO NOT EAT!
+4 Fuel

name: Solar Honeycomb
description:
Too hot for the honey extractor.
+10 Fuel

description: This honeycomb has high titanium contents. Increases electric resistance

name: Tungsten Honeycomb
description: This honeycomb has high tungsten contents. Increases protection.

name: Violium Honeycomb
description: A honeycomb with high violium contents. Increases energy max.

name: Volcanic Honeycomb
description: A volcanic honeycomb. Try placing it in a centrifuge! Good fire proofing.

name: Basic Frame
description: Basic frame for an apiary.

name: Bee Flower Head
description: The head of a Bee flower. Contains traces of anti-mite poison!

name: S.S.D (Kevin's Flesher (tm))
description: Use this on your ship to upload the ship data to S.A.I.L making it able to be used by new characters.

name: Agaran Sellsword Contract
description: Hires an Agaran sellsword to fight alongside you. Gives 10% poison resistance.

name: Arctic Contract
description: Hires an arctic explorer that provides 30% Cold resistance and reduces ship fuel costs by 8%.

name: Biohazard Contract
description: Hires a Biohazard specialist. Provides 30% Radiation resistance, and increase your ship's fuel capacity by 340.

name: Bounty Contract
description: Hires a lethal bounty hunter that talks loudly and carries a big gun.

name: Chef Contract
description: Hires an apprentice chef to keep you slightly fed and reduce fuel costs by 2%.

name: Sous Chef Contract
description: Hires a Sous Chef to keep you stuffed and reduce fuel costs by 6%.

name: Chemist-A Contract
description: Hires a chemist that boosts your jump power.

name: Chemist-B Contract
description: Hires a chemist that increases your speed.

name: Chemist-C Contract
description: Hires a chemist that gives you free rage-drugs. Sweet.

name: Chemist-D Contract
description: Hires a chemist that helps you see in the dark.

name: Collector Contract
description: Loves to hurl his balls at things until they crawl inside. Also provides a 2% fuel cost reduction and a useful Thorns effect.

name: Counsellor Contract
description: Counsellor are quite useful - they can keep madness at bay! They also provide 2% reduced fuel cost.

name: Ship Psychologist Contract
description: Mental health expert. Reduces madness effects up to 40%. Reduces fuel costs by 2%.

name: Ship Psychiatrist Contract
description: Master brain-healer-guy. Reduces madness effects up to 65%. Reduces fuel costs by 2%.

name: Cultist Contract
description: Hires a flesh-hungry cultist. Increases max ship fuel by 150 and provides Insanity Immunity and Moderate Poison Protection.

name: Cyborg Contract
description: Hires a deadly cyborg. Reduces ship mass by 10%, increases ship speed by 1.25 and grants Aether Immunity.

name: Engineer Contract
description: Hires an engineer to increase ship speed by 3.75 and reduce fuel costs by 10%.

name: Engineer II Contract
description: Provides 20% reduced fuel costs, and +3.75 ship speed.

name: Beeguy Contract
description: BZZ BZZZ! BEE ENGINES PROVIDE 2 SHIP SPEED! BEES DON'T STING

name: Hunter Contract
description: Hires a hunter. Provides Burning, Proto Poison, jungle and mud slow immmunities.

name: Alpaca Contract
description: Hires a tough Alpaca warrior.

name: Gas Specialist Contract
description: Hires a gas specialist to boost max ship fuel by 200 and grant Gas Immunity.

name: Geologist Contract
description: Sells useful resources.

name: Ghostbuster Contract
description: Hires a Ghostbuster. Provides Immunity to Erchius Ghosts, and increase your ship's fuel capacity by 340.

name: Guardian Contract
description: Impressive defensive crewmate. Provides a massive Defense Boost and 5% increased fuel efficiency.

name: Hobo Contract
description: Hires... a homeless guy that pukes on things. Increases max fuel by 250, but constantly makes you drunk.

name: Custodian Contract
description: Has a mop. Sweeps. Reduces ship mass by 10%.

name: Kirhosi Hacker Contract
description: Hire a Kirhosi Hacker on the run from the law, to increase ship speed by 3.75, grant 30% Electric resistance and protection from electrical storms.

name: Magical Girl Contract
description: A magic girl with a staff. Provides Shadow Taint and Caliginous Gas Immunity, and 5% reduced fuel costs.

name: Mechanic Contract
description: Hires a mechanic to reduce ship mass by 20% and fuel costs by 10%.

name: Mechanic II Contract
description: Reduces fuel costs by 20% and decreases ship mass by 20%.

name: Medic Contract
description: Hires a medic to help keep you alive and kicking.

name: Medic Contract II
description: Hires a combat medic to help keep you alive and kicking. Heals more quickly, but less on-ship regen.

name: 80s Metalhead Contract
description: Dude. 4% reduced fuel costs. Rock on.

name: Oceanographer Contract
description: Hires an Oceanographer to help you swim much faster, and provides Lava and Liquid Nitrogen immunity.

name: Outlaw Contract
description: Hires a ruthless outlaw companion.

name: PLUR Contract
description: The danciest companion in the universe, with booze and 4% reduced fuel costs.

name: Precursor Drone Control Chip
description: The control chip for a Precursor Drone, able to increase fuel efficiency by 10%, protect you with 30% Shadow resistance and Shadow Taint immunity, and grant +3 passive research.

name: X'ian Explorer Contract
description: Hires a unique, powerful crew member that provides a 20% reduction to fuel costs and Extreme Radiation Immunity

name: Researcher Contract
description: Hires a field researcher to take notes on the worlds you explore. +1 passive research - doesn't stack.

name: Drug Specialist Contract
description: Hires a drug specialist to increase jump height and speed, and reduces your ship's fuel costs by 5%.

name: Scuba Contract
description: Hires a Marine Biologist to help you swim faster.

name: Assassin Contract
description: Hires a deadly assassin. Grants Poison and Bio Ooze Immunity, and 160 ship maximum fuel.

name: Tailor Contract
description: Hires a tailor to keep your crew looking great.

name: Volcanologist Contract
description: Hires a volcanologist to provide 30% Fire resistance and reduce ship mass by 20%.

name: Warrior Contract
description: Hires an inexperienced warrior to fight alongside you.

name: Veteran Contract
description: Hires an experienced warrior to fight alongside you.

name: General Contract
description: Hires a hardened general to fight at your side.

name: Pro Fishing Rod
description: A pro-level rod with long line length and fast reeling time. Also durable.

name: Crystal Light
description: Shining, shimmering splendour

name: Ghost Lantern
description: Said to repel moon ghosts and punish those who harm you.

name: Khe's Ghost Lantern
description: It's covered in what appears to be drool, and rustles when you shake it.

name: Tacti-Cool Mug
description: Infinite Beer + Flashlight. What could be better?

name: Fossil Hammer
description: Not at all precise, but smacks stone well!

name: Microparticle Brush
description: Impossibly precise.

name: Hookshot
description: It pulls you up automatically! Upgrade using your Tricorder.

name: Launch Hookshot
description: You cheated to get this. You're a butthole.

name: Precursor Hookshot
description: Be careful not to get whiplash.

name: Elder Hook
description: A grappling hook dripping with...stuff. Has strange properties.

name: Ice Axe
description: Useful for extremely short-ranged grappling. Survival tool. Can also do 5 damage.

name: Bloodhook
description: Short-ranged grapple. Regenerates health when attached. Improves healing.

name: Lasher Hook II
description: A more advanced lasher hook that also deals more damage. Weighted.

name: X'ian Grapple Vine
description: A useful genetic trick of the X'i.

name: Nano-Tether
description: An amazing grappler. Use carefully, as it is very fast.

name: Energy Tether
description: An amazing grappler that regenerates your energy when extended.

name: Shadow Line
description: Siphons light and converts it to food when extended.

name: Web Shooter
description: Well, that's pretty useful. And a bit horrifying. Weighted.

name: Bizarre Erotica
description: A book that pairs a sapient being with a random mythological creature.

name: Bizarre Fiction
description: Weird fiction that is completely bonkers.

name: Blinding Envelope
description: Any time you glance at it, you are blinded for a moment.

name: Blood Ritual
description: Channel the Old Ones thoughts into your mind.

name: A Bloody Finger
description: It looks identical to your index finger.

name: All About Bees
description: This is the Bee Movie script. Over and over again.

name: Stench Candle
description: Smells exactly like corpses, and your grandfathers house.

name: Strange Carving
description: This symbol tingles your memories, but you can't quite place where you've seen it.

name: A Chipotle Coupon (2 for $24.99)
description: The fact that this place still exists is maddening.

name: A Comb
description: This comb exudes unimaginable menace.

name: Crayon of Lies
description: Anything written or drawn with it is a lie.

name: Odd Glyph
description: A strange language is carved around the edge of this disk, whispering into your mind.

name: Impossible Theories
description: Flying in the face of reason, this book of your theories is utterly insane.

name: Insane Notes
description: Your lab notes. Thoroughly nutters.

name: Law and Order
description: A law book that encourages committing arson.

name: Unimaginable Equations
description: This math is so outlandish as to be offensive. It's also *right*.

name: Creepy Mask
description: This unsettling mask it eerily cheery. It gazes back.

name: Strange Glyph
description: A strange language is carved around the edge of this disk, whispering into your mind.

name: Unknown Artifact
description: You have no idea what deity these markings praise, but it isn't pretty.

name: Glowing Glyph
description: Crackling with horrible energy and malign promise. Edible.

name: Forgotten Knowledge
description: Strange experiments long forgotten, involving bizarre devices and theories.

name: Strange Statue
description: The angles of this carving are all wrong, making you violently hallucinate.

name: Map of the Dreamlands
description: Gazing at this hurts your brain.

name: Mirror of Vision
description: Reflects only things you hate.

name: Confusing Dust

name: Mysterious Parcel

name: A Sharpened Mouse
description: A rather unusual choice in weaponry.

name: Stick of Truth
description: A mere glance at this compels you to be truthful.

name: A Terracotta Bust
description: Whatever being this represents is unknown, but it chills you.

name: Three Coins
description: No matter how much you try, they cannot be spent.

name: A Good Luck Tonsil
description: So long as you hold this, the deceased have great luck.

name: Undulating Meat
description: This unusual meat never rots and constantly undulates in fear.

name: Universal Parking

name: Vile Conch

name: Voynich Manuscript
description: What does it mean? How can it be translated?

name: Inspired Painting
